4,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":13,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":22,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Matthew de Rixton was born in 1315, in Lancashire, England, his father, Richard de Rixton, was 35 and his mother, Avina De Anyers, was 64. He had at least 1 son with Isabell de Rixton. He died in 1372, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1315–1372":"1315–1372","1320–1397":"1320–1397","1337–1399":"1337–1399","1280–1332":"1280–1332","1251–1330":"1251–1330","1330":"1330","1372":"1372","1251":"1251","1280":"1280","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1453":"1453","1397":"1397","1320":"1320","From 1337 to 1357":"1337 kuni 1357","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Rixton, Lancashire, England":"Rixton, Lancashire, England","Rixton with Glazebrook, Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1315–1372":"1315–1372","1320–1397":"1320–1397","1337–1399":"1337–1399","1280–1332":"1280–1332","1251–1330":"1251–1330","1330":"1330","1372":"1372","1251":"1251","1280":"1280","1315":"1315","1337":"1337","1399":"1399","1332":"1332","1453":"1453","1397":"1397","1320":"1320","From 1337 to 1357":"